You are working on a university refactoring architecture project.

Global rules:
1. Do not generate code that directly uses external databases, network APIs or cloud services.
2. All persistence must go through repository interfaces or in-memory repository implementations.
3. Every new business rule must have tests before or together with implementation.
4. Prefer TDD: red, green, refactor.
5. Do not place business logic in models or repositories. Put it into services.
6. Keep SOLID principles: especially Single Responsibility and Dependency Inversion.
7. Use TypeScript strict mode and avoid `any`.
8. Any new pattern must be documented in docs/architecture.md.
9. Every generated feature must include edge cases and negative tests.
10. CI must keep generating junit.xml, coverage XML/LCOV and HTML coverage reports.
